[Main Street, Gatehouse]
Here is where the hustle and bustle of the city moves towards the wilderness 
outside.  West of here lies the bazaar where a lot of the cities commerce 
takes place, the street between here and there is almost always chaotic.  
Looming to the east is the newly built inner gate of the massive gatehouse.
You see a trader. 
Obvious exits: west.
> w
w
[Main Street]
This bustling area near the city gate is where the recently constructed
street of Ferumbras' Folly joins with Main Street.  Various merchants and
visitors pass by going both in and out under the watchful eye of the
Lawkeeps, Crimson Band and the Royal Guards.
Obvious exits: south, east, west.
> w

A trader arrives.
> w
[Main Street]
This wide street cuts directly from the bazaar to the city gates. People flow 
back and forth between the two, some clad in flashy finery, others in 
utilitarian work clothes and a few in rags and tatters. As the opposite moving
throngs side step and slow up to avoid each other, little currents and eddies 
form in the stream of people.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Main Street]
Bazaar-bound throngs of people start craning their heads here in a mostly
futile attempt to see where their needed vendor is located on this day.
Those beings moving towards the gate concentrate on dodging the ones not
paying attention heading the other way.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Bazaar East]
This is the eastern most edge of the bazaar. Here a variety of street 
merchants, with wares both mundane and fantastic, set up their booths daily in
an attempt to make a living. At the corner stands run-down yet cozy inn know 
as the the Sojourner's Hospice. A door leads in.
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northwest, southwest.
> w
w
This is here because I am trying to tack on THIS (wooden) Adjective[Bazaar
Center]
The center of the bazaar bustles with activity. From the sizzle of roast 
mutton on spits, to the cries of hawkers there is almost too much for the 
senses to absorb. Apart from the interruption of merchants offering you their
wares, one might spend an enjoyable afternoon here. Many street performers, 
from jugglers to minstrels, amuse the crowds gathered near a large marble 
fountain.
A wooden bin is here.
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northeast, northwest, southeast,
southwest.
> w
w
[Bazaar West]
The Armorer's Guild makes an impressive showing with row upon row of weapons 
and armor on display. The guild buys old and damaged weapons and melts them 
down to make new ones. They manage to make use of a surprising variety of 
items bought from local adventurers. You can look up prices and inventory from
a manuscript on the table. Main Street continues to the west behind the
stalls.
Obvious exits: north, south, east, west, northeast, southeast.
