[Kai's Corner]
This busy intersection was recently expanded to allow for higher traffic.
Main Street used to end here, but has been extended to go further west.
A short ways down the street, you can see the twin towers that guard
the palace gate.  Main Street runs east and west of here, Commerce Street
begins here and leads southwest while Pleasant Street moves south.  A
platinum plaque adorns the side of the newly constructed Royal Barracks.
Obvious exits: south, east, west, southwest.
> w
w
[Main Street]
This newly built road leads between Kai's Corner and the palace.  The
cobbles are freshly laid and tightly packed.  Several buildings are in
construction here, but you can see the newly finished Royal Barracks
on the north side of the street slightly east of here.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Main Street]
Obvious exits: east, west.
