e
[Broadway]
Just off Church Street, but far enough away from the poor quarter to be 
considered decent, many of Fayd's merchant citizens have made their homes. 
Rows of spartan town houses line the street. As you pass, the various sounds 
and smells of domesticity compete for your attention: the cry of an infant, 
the whisk of a broom and the snoring of the elderly.
Obvious exits: east, west.
