nw
[Hadan Kentarus Avenue]
Hadan Kentarus Avenue begins here, the partially completed walkway has been
made from various triangularly cut stones with smaller pebbles filling the
space between them. Over an open doorway, a wooden sign proudly reads,
"The Scrivener's". Opposite it, a wrought iron fence surrounds what appears
to be a sidewalk cafe, to which a decorated arch provides entrance. Next
to the doorway, a gate leads into a small wooden building.
Obvious exits: northwest, southeast.
