[Park Avenue]
Trim hedges, backed by groves of rosewood and oak, border the street. The
smell of new-mown grass tickles your nose. Most people consider the park one of
the
most inviting parts of Fayd and have built their residences here. One of the
more eccentric residents has constucted a doorless tower as a home.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Park Avenue]
Rows of violets and roses grow by the side of the road. Grape vines have 
nearly overtaken a quaint gazebo just off to the north. One may enter the 
gazebo through a wooden arch. By the side of the road, a small flower stand 
has been set up. A sign displays the prices of the different flowers for sale.
A little path leads off towards some bleachers across the grass.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Park Ave]
The beautiful park which gives Park Avenue it's name, surrounds you. A pair
of retired adventurers feed a few pigeons from a nearby park bench. Beyond
the bench, you see a group of children taking advantage of the park's many 
trees to play a game of goblin hunt.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Park Avenue]
The park itself, beginning to green up, lies off to the east. To the west,
Park Avenue leads into the aristocratic neighborhoods. A huge marble building
looms over you, bearing an sign with tastefully engraved script reading,
"Randolphs." A modest oaken building lies opposite the jewelry store.
Obvious exits: east, west.
