w
[Park Avenue]
The road begins to slop up a green hill, from the top of which you can
overlook the fringes of a grand estate. Intricate topiary of verdant serpents.
heroes, and beasts grace the landscape. A lilac edged path winds off to the
east.
Obvious exits: east, southwest.
> sw
sw
[Park Avenue]
The avenue narrows as it proceeds through the estate. A crystal fountain 
stands by the side of the road, depicting a beautiful nymph spitting water 
into a pool.
Obvious exits: east, west, southwest.
> w
w
[Hardwood Avenue]
Hardwood Avenue is one of the most exclusive neighborhoods in all of Fayd. 
Large brick walls and guarded gateways help ensure the privacy of the nobles
who make their home here. The wealth displayed by the elaborate estates is
breath taking. The avenue upon which you travel is made of yellowish bricks
but you feel confident that if the residents of this neighborhood chose to,
they could pave the avenue with bricks of solid gold.
To the west, Hardwood Avenue continues and to the east, Hardwood intersects
Park.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Hardwood Avenue]
As you continue to move along Hardwood Avenue, a particulary old mansion 
reminds you of the rumors you have heard of several of the large estates
being haunted in this section of the city. Some of the ancient beautiful 
estates along the avenue predate even the cataclysm and if spirits prefer
to dwell in any section of town, this is probably it.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Hardwood Avenue]
A feud seems to have broken out between the estates on the north side of
Hardwood Avenue and the estates on the south side of the avenue. The feud, 
as far as you can tell, is over which side of the avenue can build the tall-
est structure. As you travel along the avenue you are witness to a progres-
sion of taller and taller towers. The tallest of the spires is still in
mid-construction.  Somewhat shorter but no less elaborate homes can be seen
to the east and the west as Hardwood Avenue continues.
Obvious exits: east, west.
> w
w
[Hardwood Avenue]
Hardwood Avenue stretches out beofre you to the east and west. The beautiful
estates are kept mostly private from the general population of Fayd. Guarded
gateways and large walls help ensure the privacy of the nobles who live here.
To the north, Manor Row with it's beautiful homes looks somewhat less 
unfriendly.
Obvious exits: north, east, west.
