[Park Avenue]
The previous end to Park Avenue, the old gate has been reworked into a stone
arch that leads south into the newly constructed Kentaur Courtyard.  Palatial
government buildings dominate this section of Park Avenue. The small army of
bureaucrats and minor nobles who keep the city running work here. These newer
buildings are marvels of post-cataclysmic architecture, with spiring marble
columns and large beautiful windows. Tall healthy elm trees line the avenue
at precisely measured intervals.  Recessed into the wall to the left of the
arch is a large polished mirmach door with a stylized desert rose artfully
engraved into its surface.
Obvious exits: south, northeast.
